A browser is a software application used to locate, retrieve and display content on the World Wide Web, including Web pages, images, video and other files. It functions by using a group of structured codes which perform a series of tasks to display a web page on the screen. The server sends the information back to the Web browser which displays the results on the browser.
I most often use google chrom but occasionally have safari automatically open from another app on my iphone and therfore see information there. 
Markup language is a system for organizing and annotating a document through the use of tage. This alows form web developement in an organized universal way in HTML, XML, and SGML.
